1. An employee has a name, a department, a salary, and years of experience.
2. A company has a name and a list of employees.
3. The bonus rate is: 15 if experience above 10, 10 if above 5, otherwise 5.
4. The bonus amount is the salary times the bonus rate divided by 100.
5. An employee is senior when they have more than 10 years of experience.
6. An employee is eligible for promotion when they are senior and in the engineering department.
7. A company has senior talent when any of its employees are senior.
8. A company is fully senior when all of its employees are senior.
